post_text:
The NHS Music Department invites you to its annual Small Ensemble Night concerts on Thursday, February 4 and Tuesday, February 9. Both shows are at 7pm in the NHS Auditorium and are free and open to the public.

These concerts are a unique and innovation portion of our season - very few secondary schools incorporate chamber music into their ensemble classes, and most of those do so only with their most advanced students. Here, we require all students to participate in the small, self-directed ensemble experience, in order to help them develop skills related to leadership, teamwork, critical listening, diagnosis, independence and interpretation of the notation and terminology that make up a musical score.

The resulting performances are always diverse and exciting, with something for everyone to enjoy. Also, each evening features its own unique set of performers and repertoire, so you can come to both nights and hear something new each time. We hope to see you there!

NHS Music is proud to invite you to our annual Fall Concerts, the first performances of the 2015-2016 Norwell Arts season!

On Tuesday, October 20th, the NHS Symphonic Band and Wind Ensemble will take to the stage, presenting works by Tchaikovsky, Mozart, Ravel and more. On Tuesday, October 27th, the NHS Chorus, Jazz Ensemble and Jazz Workshop will perform a huge range of repertoire from classical to the present.

Both concerts begin at 7pm in the NHS Auditorium, run roughly an hour in length, and are, as always, free of charge and open to the public. Hope to see you there!

Norwell Public Schools is accepting registrations for the 2015-2016 preschool lottery!

The preschools, located at Cole & Vinal Schools, are integrated programs for 3 and 4 year old students. There is a fee for attendance. Three year old students attend three morning per week (Tuesday-Thursday) and 4 year old students attend four afternoons per week (Tuesday - Friday). Space is limited.

A student who enters the program as a three-year-old student is entitled to remain in the program until he/she reaches school age.

Please visit our website www.norwellschools.org to submit a registration form. The registration period is through January 26, 2015. The lottery will be held January 27, 2015.

Our full-day kindergarten lottery for the 2015-2016 school year opens in January 2015.

post_text:
The NHS Music Department invites you to its two annual Winter Concerts, on Thursday, December 11 (Wind Ensemble/Symphonic Band) and Tuesday, December 16 (Chorus/Jazz Workshop/Jazz Ensemble). Both shows are at 7pm in the NHS Auditorium and are free of charge and open to the public.

The bands concert features a wide range of repertoire, from Renaissance dance music to an excerpt from a Bach cantata, a powerful Russian Orthodox hymn, and a Japanese fantasy reminiscent of the films of Hayao Miyazaki. The choral and jazz concert is similarly diverse, with a mix of motets, carols, Broadway show-stoppers, and a traditional spread of jazz standards from the big band and workshop combos.

We hope you'll join us to see what our students have been up to for the last seven weeks or so and to enjoy two evenings of high quality music!

Norwell High School's theater company, the Fourth Wall Players, will present The Laramie Project on December 4, 5 and 6 at 7 Pm in the NHS Auditorium. The play exposes the prejudice and hatred which led to the brutal murder in 1998 of gay student Matthew Shepard in Wyoming, and by inference takes a firm stance for tolerance, acceptance and diversity.

Norwell High School Arts hopes that the Norwell community will get solidly behind this important production and support the show and the important humanitarian cause it represents.

Tickets are $12 for adults and $5 for seniors and students and can be purchased at the box office an hour before performance time.

post_text: There will be NO SCHOOL tomorrow, Tuesday, October 30, 2012. There are a number of homes without power and a number of streets blocked by downed trees and power lines. Clean-up will begin in the morning, making running buses a challenge. We hope everyone made it through the storm safely and we look forward to seeing everyone on Wednesday morning!

post_text:
The Norwell High School Art Department presents its annual Fine Arts Festival 2012 on Thursday April 26th at 6:30 PM in the Norwell High School gymnasium. The Festival will feature art work by high school students, and will include a sample of elementary and middle school student art work as well. Music will be provided by the NHS Jazz Combo. Refreshments will be served, and the event will conclude with an awards ceremony. Please come and enjoy a great family event !!

The Fine Arts Festival is sponsored in part by the Norwell PTO and the Norwell Scholastic Arts Society.

Just a reminder about the screening of the film, Race to Nowhere, being held at the NHS auditorium this Thursday evening.

Tickets to the film are limited by the seating capacity of the auditorium. If you are planning to attend the showing, we ask that you be sure to print and bring your ticket or confirmation email. The film is scheduled to begin at 7PM. Please plan to arrive early to facilitate seating.

We look forward to sharing this film with the community!

The new, K-12 inclusive Norwell Scholastic Arts Society (NSAS) will be holding its second organizational meeting of the school year this upcoming Tuesday, November 15th at 7pm in the Vinal School Cafeteria. The meeting is open to anyone with an interest in strengthening arts education in our schools, whether they have children in grades K-12 or not.

For more information about NSAS and its mission, please visit www.norwellarts.com. If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to contact NSAS via email at norwellarts@gmail.com.

post_text:
Please join us tomorrow night for our PUBLIC EDUCATION FORUM. At this Forum, community leaders, parents, and residents will have an opportunity to “peak under the hood” of our schools. The attendees will experience what it is like to sit in an elementary, middle and high school classroom. You will be able to participate in science, English and mathematics lessons, and maybe even take a quiz!

Also this is the time to assist the Norwell School Committee and Leadership Team by sharing your ideas on how we can help all students meet 21st Century Learning Expectations. How do you think our schools are doing? Are we truly preparing students for their future? What are we missing? What resources are needed?

Join us tomorrow night (Thursday October 6, 2011) at 7:00 p.m. at Norwell Middle School. We hope to see you then!! (Thanks Allison!!)

3rd Annual "Nearly New Sale" sponsored by NHS Boosters & Vinal School - Saturday September 24, 2011 9:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. - Sparrell Gymnasium.

The sale will be featuring all kinds of used sporting goods and equipment - from baseball gloves to roller-blades to lacrosse sticks. In addition, there will be gently used Halloween costumes just in time for the holiday!
For your shopping pleasure, there will also be a bake sale.

All proceeds go to Vinal School and Norwell Boosters.
